main event: A witness observed a UFO in March 1966 in Sylvania, Ohio, and took pictures of it.
interesting points: Only one witness reported seeing the UFO,The witness had photographs of the UFO developed but did not return them after a request from Project Blue Book, The physical evidence was deemed insufficient as no further data was provided, A letter was sent to the witness requesting additional information for photo analysis, The conclusion of the report indicates insufficient data for evaluation.
witness description: The witness took photographs and had a keen interest in gathering information about UFOs.
